ABUJA – The former Chief of Staff to ex-governor Rochas Okorocha of Imo State, Uche Nwosu, has commended the former Speaker of the House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila, over his appointment as Chief of Staff to President Bola Tinubu. Nwosu, in a statement soon after the appointment was announced by Abiodun Oladunjoye, Director of Information in the presidency, said that Gbajabiamila’s political experience over the years makes him “perfectly fit into your new position as the Chief of Staff to the President”. The former Imo’s CoS statement also noted that Gbajabiamila’s “intervention in the 8 months long ASUU and FG impasse was what saved the Nigerian University system from total collapse. This is highly remarkable”. Insisting that he is a bridge builder whose appointment is well deserved and that it is a true reflection of the fact that, “the reward for hard work is more work,” the statement added, “On behalf of my family and the Board of the Ugwumba Center for Leadership Development in Africa, I want to congratulate my friend, Rt. Hon. Femi Gbajabiamila on his appointment as the Chief of Staff to the President of the Federal Republic of Nigeria. “Your sojourn in the Federal House of Representatives has contributed immensely to the development of our country, Nigeria having served as Minority Whip; Minority Leader; Opposition Leader; Majority Leader and finally as Hon. Speaker. “I rejoice with you, my brother and friend and I look forward to seeing you assist the President in unifying our dear country. Once again, congratulations, the bridge builder and unifier”.